Name: To Kill a Mockingbird
Author: Harper Lee
Description: A gripping, heart-wrenching, and wholly remarkable tale of coming-of-age in a South poisoned by virulent prejudice.

Author: George Orwell
Description: A novel about the dangers of totalitarianism, 1984 presents a dystopian future under a totalitarian regime.

Name: Pride and Prejudice
Author: Jane Austen
Description: One of the most universally loved and admired English novels, Pride and Prejudice is a sparkling comedy of manners.

Name: The Great Gatsby
Author: F. Scott Fitzgerald
Description: A portrait of the Jazz Age in all of its decadence and excess, Gatsby captured the spirit of the author's generation.

Name: The Catcher in the Rye
Author: J.D. Salinger
Description: A novel about teenage rebellion and angst, The Catcher in the Rye is a classic coming-of-age story.

Name: Moby-Dick
Author: Herman Melville
Description: The voyage of the whaling ship Pequod, led by Captain Ahab who is intent on hunting the white whale, Moby-Dick.

Name: War and Peace
Author: Leo Tolstoy
Description: A sweeping epic of Russian society during the Napoleonic era, War and Peace is a masterpiece of historical fiction.

Name: The Odyssey
Author: Homer
Description: An epic poem that tells the story of Odysseus's ten-year journey home after the Trojan War.

Name: Crime and Punishment
Author: Fyodor Dostoevsky
Description: A psychological drama that explores the moral dilemmas of crime, guilt, and redemption.

Name: The Lord of the Rings
Author: J.R.R. Tolkien
Description: An epic fantasy trilogy that follows the journey to destroy the One Ring and save Middle-earth.

Name: Jane Eyre
Author: Charlotte BrontÃ«
Description: A novel that follows the experiences of Jane Eyre, an orphaned girl who becomes a governess and falls in love with her employer.

Name: The Hobbit
Author: J.R.R. Tolkien
Description: The prelude to The Lord of the Rings, The Hobbit tells the story of Bilbo Baggins's adventure to reclaim a lost kingdom.

Name: Brave New World
Author: Aldous Huxley
Description: A dystopian novel set in a future world where technology and conditioning dictate human behavior.

Name: The Divine Comedy
Author: Dante Alighieri
Description: An epic poem that takes the reader on a journey through Hell, Purgatory, and Heaven.
